      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please don't be so cautious; you'll be running errands for the next decade! With CKD, Advil (ibuprofen) is a non-starter because it can be harsh on your kidneys. Instead, try a dose of acetaminophen, but you must take it with a splash of water and follow the instructions exactly. If the headache persists, it's a sign you need to *really* focus on your hydration!",
